The Vibrators are an original and long-lived British punk rock band that formed in 
1976.The band was founded by Ian &#039;Knox&#039; Carnochan, bassist Pat Collier, guitarist 
John Ellis, and drummer John &#039;Eddie&#039; Edwards. They first came to public notice at 
the 100 Club when they backed Chris Spedding in 1976. On Spedding&#039;s recommendation, Mickie Most signed them to his record label RAK. Most produced their first single, "We Vibrate". The band also backed Spedding on his single, "Pogo Dancing".
